subSections.title: Alternative forms
subSections.text: Due to {{w|Han unification}}, both {{w|Traditional Chinese|traditional}} and {{w|Simplified Chinese|simplified form}} (containing {{l|mul|晉}} and {{l|mul|晋}} respectively) are encoded under the same [[code point]]. Depending on the font installed, this character may appear to be either <font size=4.5, lang="zh-hant">溍</font> or <font size=4.5, lang="zh-hans">溍</font>.
